        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 24 at 8:30PM CDT until April 24 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Beaver County in the Panhandle of Oklahoma...

* Until 900 PM CDT.

* At 829 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Bryans
Corner, or 18 miles north of Perryton, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Balko and Boyd.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for the Panhandle
of Oklahoma.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
